Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The best of three set match.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka's service. Play.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.74,0:04:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Magic Girl that comes from the Orient, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.07,0:04:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a bit too soon for you \Nto stand on this court?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.20,0:04:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly, \Nhow did Belle perform in semifinals?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.35,0:04:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Physical force of a man, \Nwon't ever let slide a light-headed serve.{simple words, slightly confusing meaning: 腕力は男並み甘いサーブは通じない}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.81,0:04:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If she doesn't secure the first serve, \Nthis will turn into a messy match.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.04,0:04:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down... \NI have to calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Oka! \NThis kind of second serve will never do{/ This is too strong for a second serve; I can't fully figure one word and you probably know which one}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.83,0:04:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No good! Course is light-headed. \NYou'll be stopped in your tracks at once!{guessing that "jitande" part; tried to include "legs" somehow and this is the best I could come up with}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.64,0:04:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,One more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.41,0:04:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.81,0:04:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Toss with more precision!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.39,0:04:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Twist your hips more! \NBe light in your balance!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.28,0:04:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's always excusable \Nto use the second serve, don't you?{/ You need to stop always taking the second serve for granted. / You will not be forever allowed to use second serve, understood?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.30,0:04:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{wjat the actual fuck is this rap god sequense, I'm tthis close to shooting myself}Hit your first serve with confidence, \Nlike that of your second serve!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit your more powerful first serve \Nwithout hesitation!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.69,0:04:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.91,0:04:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Repeat it over and over \Nuntil you do it reflexively!{/ acquire it yourself! / make it yours! - needless to say I still hardly grasp a single word of Munakata's gibberish here; it feels like seiyu's been paid per second of final recording so they decided to save on Munakata's cut}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.57,0:05:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this serve?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.69,0:05:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.22,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is some nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.88,0:05:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm wide open!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.37,0:05:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How can this be? \NSuch power in that petite body?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,15-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.10,0:05:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Her getting in this final round \Nwas by no means a fluke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression of #1 Seed{however I look at this "sheedo" it makes no sense, so for now my logical chain is: she's the preeminent contender -> #1 in tournament seeding chart -> "first seed" - which reminds me that probably a tl note explaining seeding may make sense here, since seeding would be mentioned in OVA2 as well as later through the ep} just changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.69,0:05:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.41,0:05:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to your and Munakata's hard work, \Nthe US #1 Seed is now compelled to fight you as equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,While you are free to fight any way you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This legacy is what one man named Munakata Jin \Nhas been honing until the very last flicker of his life,{this is literal af}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.61,0:05:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.78,0:06:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This feels so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.24,0:06:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My body moves like a perfect image!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.61,0:06:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hit an ace. \NShe won't let me score at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.07,0:06:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But I cannot lose! \NAfter all, I am the #1 Seed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.26,0:06:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She got this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Game. 6 to 4. Set -{/ for} Belle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This may have turned the tide completely just now!{/ She totally hit the opposite side just now! / This [match] just went in a totally wrong direction!; this line is too perplexing, I'm still wondering about the real meaning of 今のは完全に逆を突いたのに}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still Oka who sets the pace of the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.37,0:06:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She will take the next set.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.24,0:06:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.04,0:07:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This feels great, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.53,0:07:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I can move \Nexactly the way you taught me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.56,0:07:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll come home soon{guess, can't get that "torae" part}. \NIn the span of the next two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a big turmoil will follow, \Nfor you will no longer be gone just for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.26,0:07:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, the person who is coming home \Ndepends on you even more than I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.06,0:07:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Till later, Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.24,0:07:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, it's my turn to become a Demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.09,0:07:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.25,0:07:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.37,0:08:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.20,0:08:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.53,0:08:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She stopped halfway, going for that ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.45,0:08:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Something was off just now. \NIn the last point, with Oka...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.39,0:08:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka must have injured her knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.32,0:08:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Bell, what's the matter? You're not your usual self. \NBut instead, you're terrified!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.77,0:08:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear wells up in me,\Nbut I have to hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.79,0:08:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one still holding the points' lead, \NBelle Mackenzie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.72,0:10:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Game set. \NMatch won by Belle Mackenzie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.43,0:10:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Warmest congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.96,0:10:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope we meet again, someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.29,0:10:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just {\i1}someday{\i0}. \NWe certainly will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi Oka, please come to this year's Wimbledon \Nto be my opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I made it to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.28,0:10:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,New York adventure without Coach \Nis hereby concluded!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.51,0:10:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I return to Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.19,0:11:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Till next time, Angie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.87,0:11:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope, I come to Japan soon too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.26,0:11:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do. \NGoodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.66,0:11:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.07,0:11:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.54,0:11:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My dearest Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.96,0:11:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's winter outside. \NBut spring is always around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.73,0:11:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.89,0:11:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Only those, who endured it all the way through winter, \Ncan enjoy the warmth of spring to follow - don't forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.81,0:11:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I hold a firm belief - \Nyou are the type of person to endure it to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Deal? Whatever comes at you, \Ndon't lose your spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Coach Reynolds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Papa just say \N{\i1}My dearest Hiromi?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.99,0:11:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That time, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In the pro tournament, I was vanquished \Nand swept out with a laughable score.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.43,0:11:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in my life, \NI plunged so deep into desperation then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.17,0:11:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My dearest and only daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.11,0:11:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa also started this way \Nand so brought the tennis player in me back to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.01,0:12:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, he used this word \Nfor the second time ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.63,0:12:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be something really grave \Nabout to hit{guess; can't figure that "mimi" part in the end} Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.45,0:12:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder, where we are flying now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.99,0:12:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But either way, \NI can{ certainly} feel Japan getting closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.90,0:12:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to show it to Coach Munakata right away, \NI put the medal in the pocket on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.91,0:12:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My handmade souvenir is also here with me \Nto present it at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.53,0:12:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.91,0:12:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Though it's been just three weeks, \Nit felt like we haven't seen for a full year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.66,0:12:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you find out I was thinking about such things {[as souvenirs]}\Nduring{/instead of} matches, you'll throw a fit{/ get mad}. It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's the truth! \NI just wanted to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.57,0:13:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep well, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.53,0:13:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{Because }After this,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.01,0:13:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it would probably be a long time{he doesn't actually says about time anywhere here, but it fits well and I'm unsure how to interpret the 訪れ part}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.49,0:13:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,before you can sleep as soundly{/Lit: peacefully and soundlessly}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.00,0:13:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, your health... \NYour health finally got better?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, absolutely... \NMy condition is absolutely fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is? \NI'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.22,0:13:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.05,0:13:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Your runner up medal, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.47,0:13:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You did well.\N'Twas a fine match.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.01,0:13:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you've read the news...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.83,0:13:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I saw the match itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean, in America?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.23,0:13:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you I'd come later?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.19,0:13:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A fine match, in all truthfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.51,0:14:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, here, here! \NWelcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.25,0:14:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Oka. \NKeep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.77,0:14:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure! I mean... Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.49,0:14:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome{this word is hackneyed af at this point but I don't see a way around it} back, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.90,0:14:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even dad attends! \NI'm really home!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.39,0:14:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My, Maki, did you happen to gain some \Nwhile we haven't seen?{/ we haven't seen for some time, but aren't you a bit more plump now?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.04,0:14:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that how you treat your lifelong friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.71,0:14:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's Hiromi who has been gorging \Non America's mammoth steaks!{Hiromi herself must have feasted on enormous steaks in America.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Think again!{/ Wrong, wrong!} \NI burned{it's technically wrong to say "burn choly", but since you cannot shake it off with physical excersices anyhow, might as well play along to Hiromi's fallacy + don't wanna become a pedant here} all of my cholesterol in matches!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.26,0:14:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, what about Coach? \NCoach Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my, you really expect that Coach to be yelling \Nsomething like "Yo, welcome back!" at such a place?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- But you know...\N- Instead, hey, what about souvenirs?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.96,0:14:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking so forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.96,0:14:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This car! Hurry-scurry onboard, \NMadame Souvenir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.91,0:14:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Maki, you could use some more reserve, \Neven as a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.67,0:14:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NWho would ever want a reserved friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.45,0:15:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, I appreciate your cooperation \Nin such circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.51,0:15:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the real difficulties begin just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.19,0:15:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,4-6, 7-5 and 5-7?\NThat gold medal was so close!{/ You earned a gold medal too!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.46,0:15:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Maki, Coach has not been discharged yet?{/Hey, Maki, Coach's hospitalization is still going on?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.59,0:15:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a close checkup can't take that long!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.74,0:15:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.29,0:15:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They shouldn't have called it "close" then!{/Lit: Well, they are thorough, so, you know...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.33,0:15:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, know what? \NGoemon has become a Papa meanwhile!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.48,0:15:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, immediately after you left for America.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.51,0:15:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Hiromi, recently\Nwe received a call from some Mr. Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.22,0:15:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He now lives at Mr. Munakata's house \Nand asked you to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.73,0:15:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, so Coach is no longer hospitalized!{/Lit: So Coach was discharged after all?; I replaced "hospitalized" with "not discharged" earlier, now I returned the favor}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.63,0:15:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He must have returned home then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.67,0:15:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no need to deny it until now!{/You could have just told me it long ago.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.26,0:15:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Chauffeur, \Nplease get us to one more place.{/we need to change the destination, if you don't mind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,'Kay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.16,0:16:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You go ahead and return home. \NI've got a lot of souvenirs and reports to present to Coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.39,0:16:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.39,0:16:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... You know, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.84,0:16:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Maki?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.27,0:16:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is, \NI'll stay awake through this night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you wanna call someone, \NI'd listen to your stories gladly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.51,0:16:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NThere'll be another day full of stories tomorrow!{/You'll hear everything in person tomorrow!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.67,0:16:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.97,0:16:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Aikawa, you have our gratitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.65,0:16:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach! Coach, I knew you'd be here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.73,0:16:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm finally ba—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.21,0:16:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.77,0:16:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry,\NI mistook you for Coach just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.53,0:16:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is Coach here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.61,0:16:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.42,0:16:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.60,0:17:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have chills all over my body.{/I'm shivering violently.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.14,0:17:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, I can almost hear you wailing.{/I feel like I can hear your lamentations.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.05,0:17:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My dearest... My dearest Hiromi.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.11,0:17:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no longer a way for anybody \Nto protect her{/keep her away} from this reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.42,0:17:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.45,0:17:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got something to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.41,0:17:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.30,0:17:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A diary? Instead, can't you tell me \Nwhere Coach Munakata is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.95,0:17:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it. \NFrom where I squeezed in the bookmark{I couldn't figure wtf "koyori" is after all, but evidently it's some kind of paper}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.88,0:17:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Munakata's handwriting?\NSo it's Coach's diary...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.07,0:17:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"I took over the coaching \Nof Nishi High tennis club."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.89,0:18:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A player worth bringing up, to bet my everything on, \Nhas finally appeared.{/Lit: I finally found a player that I can train from scratch to put my everything on the line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.99,0:18:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka Hiromi. Though still crude, \NI think she has a strong natural predisposition.{/I see unrefined habits of a future genius in her.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.39,0:18:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He writes about me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.98,0:18:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,At twice the usual... No, at God knows how many times \Nthe usual speed, I will be bringing Oka up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.55,0:18:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no other way around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.59,0:18:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still to be seen \Nif she manages to keep up with such regimen.{hard to hear, hard to grasp - very vague translation but I don't see what else it can be here}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.60,0:18:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach's diary... Why now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"It seems, my time is running short eventually."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.98,0:18:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, my time is eventually running short.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.43,0:18:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharp pain - I occasionally lose consciousness. \NThree times already in this week alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.03,0:18:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,For how much longer will I last?{/Will I be able to hold on?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.08,0:18:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,December 15th.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.56,0:18:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A long-awaited letter from Daigo says, \Nin a matter of days, he'll come too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.08,0:18:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope, I'll have enough time \Nto introduce him to Oka...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.57,0:18:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.86,0:18:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Munakata, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka came to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.26,0:18:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Read further!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.37,0:19:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,For you, it is a duty \Nto read this Munakata's diary in full!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.13,0:19:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Duty?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.35,0:19:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.31,0:19:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,December 25th.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo arrived, \Naccompanied by his usual 24oz.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.50,0:19:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I could finally introduce him to Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.56,0:19:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, when I first wrote him a letter about you \Ntwo years ago, his first{I don't like to use 2 "firsts" consequently, but can't be helped imo} conclusion was that you are a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.51,0:19:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only later that his error surfaced \Nwhen he found out you're a woman.{Needless to say, Munakata's talk is still a gibberish, so here it's the latter "eera ga wateteita" part that I half-guessed; johnny's version suggests "he was utterly ashamed" which may work too though I can't subscribe to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.28,0:19:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But as of now, from your predispositions and habits \Nto your body rhythm -
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.16,0:19:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he knows you like the back of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.19,0:19:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,From 16 till 22{funnily enough, this may be both [years old] and [hours pm]; upd: nevermind, it's y.o.}, we fought others{Lit is just "formed" but I want a contrast with the other part of the sentence} in a pair, or chased the same yellow ball{he says explicitly "白球" - white ball, though the tennis one is yellow one, but I don't think it has artistical value or is important to the viewer, so yellow it is}, with net squeezed{he uses the same confusing verb as Daigo used for bookmark earlier} in between{this doesn't sound a bit gay, does it?}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.49,0:19:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And as for the next 5 years, \Nwe envisioned{I didn't really figure what 見つめる means here, reckon it's some kind of "plan / intend" but has something to do with eyes, so "envisioned" or "looked forward" should do} us spending them the exact same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.53,0:19:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,First death, then hope...\NI allude to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.29,0:19:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,December 26th - hospitalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.89,0:19:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was given 3 years at best, \Nyet I endured it all the way until today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.53,0:19:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Had I just a month more, \Nyour results from America would have come.{/ I would have at least found out how well you performed in America.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.17,0:19:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, even two weeks is enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.91,0:19:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just greeting you all \Non your everyday training{still unsure about "torei" part in the beginning} would be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.23,0:20:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, I'd send you all off \Nwithout ever giving you any idea.{/ This way, the issue would have never came to light until you're all off to USA.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.71,0:20:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Oka, I know Katsura Daigo \Nwill relieve me as your pillar of support afterwards.{/Lit: And then, Oka, after that, Katsura Daigo will prop / support you wholeheartedly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.49,0:20:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, I will be by your side \Nuntil the end of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.45,0:20:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your play is my play! \NMeeting you was the grandest blessing of my life. {Lit would be "I'm happy to have met you"; was going for a deliberate mistranslation here because I think it's more artistic and better fits such a high moment to turn this whole line into a hymnal with smt like "Thy successes are my delight." but this phrase is flashbacked in next ep unfortunately so had to scrap it altogether; also, I wanted those 2 lines to be constructed alike}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.74,0:20:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,January 15th.\NPlane{/ Departure} to US.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, aim for the ace!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.64,0:20:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Blank page?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.05,0:20:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else is written...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.73,0:20:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's next? Next? Next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.81,0:20:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, what about January 16th?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.04,0:20:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,17th? 18th?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.31,0:20:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What about January 19th?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.13,0:20:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Please show me it! \NThere has to be a diary from January 15th on!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.71,0:20:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Katsura!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.21,0:21:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At 6:37 of January 15th,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.95,0:21:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the man who was a coach to you \Nand a bosom friend to me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,stopped making new entries in his diary.{/ stopped keeping the diary. / was no longer capable of keeping a diary.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.77,0:21:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.39,0:21:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.09,0:23:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Aikawa Maki.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.21,0:23:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi is acting somehow weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.29,0:23:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She just lost someone so important to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.56,0:23:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet on the very next day \Nshe fights hard on{no idea what this "gukaketandatte" part} a training!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.97,0:23:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she really that insensitive?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.73,0:23:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, she invites me to have fun \Nin the amusement park!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.01,0:23:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of that just before the funerals...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.08,0:23:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what the heck is going on in her head?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.65,0:23:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time: Goodbye, Coach.
